component (releases with no nearby closure) changed by $[\text{X}]$
($p = [\text{X}]$). The known pre-existing component (releases on record more
than 180 days before a closure) changed by $[\text{X}]$ ($p = [\text{X}]$).

If the standalone component falls, the reform reduced leak incidence through a
channel independent of the closure margin. If only the closure-revealed component
rises, the change in total leaks is mechanical: more closures produce more
